DEFERRED follow-ups (not blocking E.5 sign-off):

  D-E.5-1  Invert worker lookup priority: workspace_browser_sites > workspaces.
           browserbase_profile_id. Today's fallback fires only when
           profile_id is null; if the workspace has both, the (potentially
           stale) workspace-wide Context wins over the per-host saved one.
           Worked around for E.5 by nulling profile_id; the deployed worker
           image (sha256:4cefa1d…) still has the bug. Fix is one block in
           worker/src/opencode-plugin/index.ts + rebuild + push.

  D-E.5-2  goto_url's detectSignInWall runs immediately after
           harnessGotoUrl (= Page.navigate, which resolves before navigation
           completes), so the detector reads about:blank or mid-redirect
           HTML and the `browser_login_required` activity event doesn't
           fire. Agent's final_answer still correctly reports the gated
           outcome via its own screenshot/js inspection (see negative-
           control run), so the user-visible result is right, but the
           structured event for UI consumers is missing on this path.
           Fix: run detector AFTER a wait_for_load + brief settle delay,
           OR poll innerText against the post-redirect URL.

  D-E.5-3  D.3 manual-trigger path doesn't inject env.automation into the
           worker's runner, so worker/src/outputs.ts dispatchOutputs is
           skipped. Other automation triggers (D.5 webhook, D.6 schedule)
           DO inject it because the cron-kicker and webhook-router are
           the dispatch path. The manual-trigger code in
           api/src/routes/automations.ts POSTs the run to SQS but doesn't
           include the automation row in the message. Fix is in the
           dispatcher Lambda payload + worker env loader.

  D-E.5-4  api/src/lib/browserbase.ts: createSession sets `userMetadata.run_id`
           to `browser-sites-connect-${host}` — not a unique id, mildly
           confusing in BB analytics if two concurrent connects fire for
           the same host. Cosmetic.

  Connect handler does NOT navigate the session to the host URL — operator
  has to type `location.href = '<host>'` in the inspector's console after
  opening the live view. The connect handler computes initialUrl in code
  but never sends it to Browserbase. Fix in the connect path: after
  createSession, POST a CDP Page.navigate to initialUrl. ~30 lines.
